  • Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
  • Melt butter and set aside.
  • Turn on a skillet or griddle to medium heat and preheat while getting batter ready.
  • Add egg yolks only to dry mix and separate egg whites into a medium glass bowl and set aside.
  • Add milk to main mix 1 cup at a time and stir.
  • Once all milk is added, stir in melted butter and set aside.
  • Now whip the egg whites until fully stiff.
  • Fold egg whites into pancake batter until well integrated.
  • Cooking surface should be up to temp now and ready. A standard large cooking spoon is about the right size to scoop batter onto cook surface. If room allows, you may cook more than one pancake at a time.
  • After 1-2 minutes, or when the top starts to have bubbles or holes, flip pancake over.
  • Cook another 1-2 minutes, or until center is fully cooked. Test the center with corner of spatula. If spatula corner comes back clean, pancake is done.
  • Butter completed pancakes and serve while hot.
